                        Rankin
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1949v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d685</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">685</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1949-11-20T22:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1949-11-20T22:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-11-20T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-11-20T22:00:00-05:00" n="685" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d685">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.001/11–2149: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hong Kong</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Rankin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hong Kong</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-21T11:00:00+08:00">November 21, 1949—11 a. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 21—3:35 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1093. Son of Li Tsung-jen informs officer of Consulate General that Li desires go
                    to States in his official capacity to seek medical treatment. Li would like to
                    travel with entourage, extent of which yet unknown, by official American
                    aircraft as did Madame Chiang Kai-shek. Will Department please advise soonest
                    reference visas and transportation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rankin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
